[[File:PitcairnStamp.jpg|150px|thumb|upright|A 1951 Pitcairn Islands definitive stamp]] The '''[[postal history]] of the [[Pitcairn Islands]]''' can be traced to second half of the 19th century, when outgoing mail was hand stamped as "Posted on Pitcairn Island: no stamps available."<ref>{{cite news|author=|title=Pitcairn’s Postal Services|publisher=Pitcairn Islands Study Center, [[Pacific Union College]]|date=|url=http://library.puc.edu/pitcairn/pitcairn/postal.shtml|accessdate=2009-03-22}}</ref> Stamps were carried by passing ships and received postal stamps and cancellation at various ports of calls.<ref name=NYT>{{cite news|author=Barth Healey|title=Stamps: Big Issues From a Small Volcanic Island in the Pacific|publisher=[[The New York Times]]|date=February 5, 1989|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1989/02/05/style/stamps-big-issues-from-a-small-volcanic-island-in-the-pacific.html|accessdate=2009-03-22}}</ref> However, this practice was discontinued in 1926 following reports of ship passengers mixing their own mail into the “no stamp” system set aside for the Pitcairn residents.<ref name=PIPB>{{cite news|author=|title=50th Anniversary of the first Pitcairn Islands Stamps|publisher=Pitcairn Islands Philatelic Bureau|date=|url=http://www.stamps.gov.pn/ann-firstPitcairnIssue.htm|accessdate=2009-03-22}}</ref>
In June 1927, a postal agency was set up on Pitcairn to sell [[New Zealand]] stamps. The first Pitcairn postage stamps, consisting of eight denominations, were issued on October 15, 1940.<ref name= NYT/>
The New Zealand-based Pitcairn Islands [[Philatelic bureau|Philatelic Bureau]] coordinates the territory’s stamp program.<ref name=PIPB/> The program issues up to six commemorative stamps per year, and new definitive stamps are issued on an average cycle of five years.<ref>{{cite news|author=Vernon N. Kisling|title=Pitcairn Islands Stamp Collecting: An Introduction|publisher=Pitcairns Island Study Group|date=|url=http://www.pisg.net/Collecting/StampIntro.htm|accessdate=2009-03-22}}</ref> The sale of philatelic issues has been a source of revenue for the territory.<ref name=NYT/>
== List of people on stamps of the Pitcairn Islands == Below is a partial list of people on stamps of the Pitcairn Islands arranged in alphabetical order:<ref>{{cite news|author=|title=Pitcairn Philately|publisher=Pitcairn Islands Study Center, Pacific Union College|date=|url=http://library.puc.edu/pitcairn/pitcairn/philately.shtml|accessdate=2009-03-22}}</ref> * [[John Adams (mutineer)|John Adams]] (1940) * [[Thomas Adams (musician)|Thomas Adams]] (1969) * [[Prince Andrew, Duke of York]] (1986) * [[Anne, Princess Royal|Princess Anne]] (1973) * Captain [[William Bligh]] (1940) * [[Marlon Brando]] 250th Anniversary (2014) * [[Charles, Prince of Wales]] (1981) * [[Fletcher Christian]] (1940) * [[Winston Churchill]] (1974) * [[Diana, Princess of Wales]] (1981) * [[Charles Dickens]] (2012) * [[Prince Edward, Earl of Wessex]] (1999) * [[Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon|Queen Elizabeth, the Queen Mother]] (1949) * [[Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom]] (1952) * [[George VI of the United Kingdom]] (1940) * [[Mel Gibson]] 250th Anniversary (2014) * [[Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh]] (1971) * [[Robert Pitcairn (midshipman)|Robert Pitcairn]] (2017) * [[Sarah, Duchess of York]] (1986) * [[Peter Scott|Sir Peter Scott]] (1992) * [[Sophie, Countess of Wessex]] (1999) * Chris Stewart (2009) * [[John I. Tay]] (1986) * [[George Washington]] (1976) * [[Simon Young (magistrate)|Simon Young]] (1961)
