{{italic title}}
[[Image:Page de garde Zeiller 13683.jpg|thumb|right|Engraved title page of first volume, ''Topographia Galliae'', 1655]]
[[image:Titre Martin Zeiller 13684.jpg |thumb|Titel]]
[[image:Page de titre Zeiller 14036.JPG |thumb|Champagne]] 
'''''Topographia Galliae''''' (1655–1661) is a German-language series of illustrated books created by engraver [[Matthäus Merian]] and writer [[Martin Zeiler]], and published in [[Frankfurt]]. It describes cities and towns in 17th-century [[History of France|France]].<ref>{{cite book |title=Universal Cyclopaedia |volume=8 |year= 1909 |publisher=D. Appleton & Co. |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=_N1TAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA40 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |author=[[Jacques Charles Brunet]] |title=Manuel du libraire et de l'amateur de livres |trans-title=Catalogue for Booksellers and Bibliophiles |edition=4th |language=French |location= Paris |publisher= Firmin Didot frères |year= 1844 |volume=5 |chapterurl=http://hdl.handle.net/2027/nyp.33433089888980?urlappend=%3Bseq=531 |chapter=Histoire de France (23133) }}</ref> [[Wenceslaus Hollar]] also contributed engravings.<ref>{{citation |title=Catalogue of Rare and Valuable Books on the Fine Arts |number=279 |year=1909 |publisher=[[Bernard Quaritch]] |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=iIkDAAAAYAAJ&pg=PA162 |quote=Zeilleri Topographia Galliae }}</ref>
{{TOC right}}

